#Part 6

[[Written on Feb 4-5, 2025]]

Int. Saylor’s Temporary House - Garage

ANNE is not around anymore.  RICK is standing in the garage next to a parked time machine, wiping the windows and mirrors.  The garage door is still up.  SAYLOR walks over to RICK.

SAYLOR
So!

RICK
Is she not joining?

SAYLOR
Nah.

RICK
Don’t put the door down.  Having a light breeze would be lovely.

SAYLOR does it anyway.  She’s in the garage and has the garage door remote.

RICK
Not a good listener, are you?

SAYLOR is silent until the garage door comes down entirely.

SAYLOR
How’s 2038?

RICK
Not again...

SAYLOR
No.  Seriously.  No irony.  What was happening there?

As they talk, SAYLOR walks around the time machine, glimpsing wires and circuits.  RICK mostly stands in one place, but occasionally he examines things too.

RICK
You know how Lisa communicates with us.  Especially me.

SAYLOR
I’ll never understand the logic of her attachment to you...  Or anyone else, for that matter.  I mean, she’s a goddamn AI.

RICK
You know she acts like she’s not.

SAYLOR
We don’t even know what time period she’s from.  Maybe she’s from an era when the distinction between man and machine has blurred completely.  What could it be, 40th century?

RICK
Earlier, I guess...

SAYLOR
We were in 2345, it’s not as advanced, she can’t be from there.

RICK
(admiringly)
You’ve learned to discern the tiniest inconsistencies in such things quite deftly.

SAYLOR
It’s... kinda obvious, really.

RICK
Nevertheless, she discovered a special, 361st Darkrock base in 2038, which we had long tried to locate by deciphering a message left in the remains of a member of an elite series of sleepwalkers.

SAYLOR
My goodness, that piece of junk is still there...

RICK
And she came up with a plan that proved to be effective.

SAYLOR
(worried)
Did you sign up for her deadly venture alone??

RICK
We had to proceed carefully, without attracting attention.  Lisa successfully found the weakest points, for which one person was enough to demolish everything down to the very foundation.  Much to the bald man’s annoyance.

SAYLOR
Always surprises me how she does that...

RICK
Remember when we were at the tech expo downtown in 2038 and she hacked the whole hackathon just for kicks-and-giggles?

SAYLOR
I would say, not just hacked.  Hacked up.

RICK
Hah, exactly.

SAYLOR
The last time she sent you on a mission, did you get caught?

RICK
Well, there was a chase, of course.

SAYLOR
Did they recognize you?

RICK
They didn’t have a chance.  I had enough time to run away far enough and I took some precautions.
(puts the hood on)
Hoodie in the dark, for instance.  Classic.

SAYLOR
One day, this trick will stop working, y’know.
(takes off RICK’s hood)
Silly you.  Don’t push your luck like that.

RICK
If it really stops, you know we’ll manage to smash ’em to pieces.  It’s gonna be an unforgettable banger.

SAYLOR
That’s the case when it’s better later than earlier, okay?

RICK
You’re brilliant enough to deal with that, easy as pie for you.

SAYLOR
(shyly)
Don’t overrate me...

RICK
Still, I’m here, perfectly safe, and they won’t recognize me once we get back there.

SAYLOR
Rare to hear your confident tone.

RICK
Be glad it happens more often than you expect.

SAYLOR
I am, Rick, I am.  But you know you always keep me on my toes.

RICK
Okay, okay.  I get your point.  Next trip will not be without your company.

SAYLOR
You better make sure of that.

RICK
Oh well, we can’t get there yet, right?

RICK checks the energy container (part of the time machine) that’s wired to something behind the garage door leading inside the house.

RICK (CONT’D)
Ah, primary energy container is still recharging.

SAYLOR
How much energy is there?

RICK
8 percent.

SAYLOR
Gonna take a while.

RICK
Lisa told me we can kick it up--

SAYLOR
(mildly angry)
--No!  No, Rick, we’re not experimenting on this machine!

RICK
Er, there’s one thing we need to do, come over here.

SAYLOR
Blue fluid compressor, I take it?

RICK
That’s the one.

SAYLOR walks over to RICK, who is standing in front of a small transparent container with a thick blue liquid.  Rods and inner tubes are submerged in the liquid.  Outside the container are outer tubes and wires.

SAYLOR
(annoyed)
Malfunctioning again?

RICK
Yeah, sorry.

SAYLOR
(punches RICK lightly on the arm)
I told you, be gentle with the fourth pedal!  You’re putting too much pressure on this device over and over again, of course it keeps playing bad tricks.  You could be sent straight to hell!

RICK
(ironizing)
I’m not a pianist one here.

SAYLOR
Except the piano only has three pedals, normally.

RICK
You could say, it’s a time machine as well.

SAYLOR
Shut up, help me pump the fluid.

SAYLOR carefully removes the tube from the device while RICK goes through the shelves of the garage.

SAYLOR
Oh blazes, it’s been leaking, hurry!!  There’s residual current in the wires!

RICK
Damn!!

SAYLOR
I’ll try to discharge.

