Things to consider maybe?

RICK
Here we go again...

RICK mouths “matchmaker”.

SAYLOR
I mean, comments don’t lie.  Not me saying that, mate.
(persuading)
Oh come on, cranky pie!  Crack a Hollywood smile!  It’s adorable!

A strained smile holds on RICK’s face for a second.  SAYLOR attentively scrolls the comments until something caught her eye.

SAYLOR
Oh dear...  Oh wowie kazowie.  If they only knew what I know, they wouldn’t even think of it.

RICK
What is it?

SAYLOR sets aside the tablet, grabs the arms of the armchair, and leans forward slightly.

SAYLOR
Three commenters genuinely want to marry you.
(reclines back in her armchair and picks up a tablet)
A-ha-ha-ha!

RICK
Seriously.  Stop browsing those sections.  I hate when you’re doing that.

SAYLOR
Listen to this one:
(clears the throat and reads dramatically)
“Rick, I wish you could stop these electromagnetic experiments.  Every damn time, you never fail to get my heart attracted to the screen.”

RICK
People are just being obsessed, it happens.

SAYLOR
Hah, dude, at this rate I’d pay with distant stars to see what you look like in a shining white jacket.

RICK rolls his eyes.

SAYLOR
(facepalming with laughter)
A-ha-ha-ha, oh dear.

RICK
(annoyed)
Saylor.

LISA abruptly intrudes into the conversation through SAYLOR’s tablet.  A young red-eyed woman with long black hair (with a faint tinge of red), gathered in a ponytail.  Wears a black jacket, white shirt and a green bow.  In her ears are golden earrings in the shape of stars.

LISA (V.O.)
Fools!

SAYLOR
Oh hey!  Lisa!  You’re late to the party!

RICK
We’ve had quite an eventful day without you, sorry.

LISA (V.O.)
(to RICK)
Oh not a problem, sweetheart.  You paid enough attention to me yesterday.  Or was it 14 years later?  Perspective is up to you.

RICK
Nice to have everyone off my back.

SAYLOR
I have a sneaking suspicion we’re not done yet, are we, Lisa?

LISA (V.O.)
The fun is just beginning and you’re already running late!!

LISA automatically turns on the CCTV view mode on SAYLOR’s tablet.  There are a few dozen sleepwalkers walking on the lawn.

SAYLOR
Not our fault.  They came in 17 minutes later than usual.
(sleepy, yawning)
I almost fell asleep.

LISA (V.O.)
Butts up!  Now!!

RICK grabs a bunch of small round bombs in his hands, holding them to his chest.  He’s rushing to the door.  SAYLOR runs over to the window, still holding the tablet in her hands and switching the app to start manually aiming the Bomb Thrower: a device in the form of a pipe mounted on a pole attached to a flat base on the lawn.

Ext. Saylor’s Temporary House - The Lawn

RICK is loading the first bomb into the Bomb Thrower and he gives SAYLOR a thumbs up.  SAYLOR’s command comes from the tablet to it, ignition is made and the bomb is fired.  Bang, a couple of slow walking robots get seriously damaged, sparks flying in a fountain, they fall on the lawn.

Int. Saylor’s Temporary House - By the Window

SAYLOR
Lisa, tell me how long they’ll last tonight.

LISA
Prediction is 2 hours and 7 minutes. Margin of error: 7 percent.

SAYLOR
Well.  This time we all will get a good night’s sleep.

